      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0002",
      "text": " 26",
      "bbox": [
        521.04,
        723.59,
        534.92,
        734.7
      ],
      "block_index": 2,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0003",
      "text": "4.2.4",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        57.65,
        118.24,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0004",
      "text": "Echo (ECHO)",
      "bbox": [
        128.24,
        57.65,
        190.94,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0005",
      "text": "4.2.4.1  Description",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        82.97,
        187.05,
        94.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0006",
      "text": "The Echo ELS requests the Recipient to transmit the Payload contents that follows the",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        106.97,
        539.96,
        118.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0007",
      "text": "ELS_Command back to the Initiator of the Echo command in the same order as received using the",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        118.97,
        539.88,
        130.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0008",
      "text": "LS_ACC Reply Sequence. The Echo ELS Request provides a means to transmit a Data frame and",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        130.97,
        539.87,
        142.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0009",
      "text": "have the Payload content returned for a simple loopback diagnostic function. The Echo command",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        142.96,
        539.82,
        154.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0010",
      "text": "shall be transmitted as a one frame Sequence and the LS_ACC Reply Sequence is also a one frame",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        154.96,
        539.98,
        166.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0011",
      "text": "Sequence.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        166.96,
        143.76,
        178.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0012",
      "text": "4.2.4.2  Protocol",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        190.96,
        172.6,
        202.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0013",
      "text": "a) Echo Request Sequence",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        214.96,
        232.98,
        226.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0014",
      "text": "b) LS_ACC or LS_RJT Reply Sequence",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        238.96,
        287.89,
        250.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0015",
      "text": "4.2.4.3  Request Sequence",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        262.96,
        221.54,
        274.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0016",
      "text": "Addressing: ",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        286.96,
        157.1,
        298.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0017",
      "text": "The D_ID field designates the destination of the request while the S_ID field designates",
      "bbox": [
        157.08,
        286.96,
        540.08,
        298.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 2
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0018",
      "text": "the source of the request.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        298.96,
        209.35,
        310.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0019",
      "text": "Payload: ",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        322.96,
        140.41,
        334.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0020",
      "text": "The format of the Payload is shown in table 7. If a Login with the destination Nx_Port does",
      "bbox": [
        140.4,
        322.96,
        540.02,
        334.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 2
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0021",
      "text": "not exist, the maximum size of the ECHO data field shall be the default Buffer-to-buffer Receive",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        334.96,
        540.01,
        346.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0022",
      "text": "Data_Field Size - 4 (i.e., 124 bytes). If a Login with the destination Nx_Port exists, the ECHO data",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        346.96,
        539.96,
        358.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0023",
      "text": "field size is limited by the smallest Receive Data_Field Size supported by the destination Nx_Port,",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        358.96,
        540.05,
        370.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0024",
      "text": "the Fabric, and the source Nx_Port for the class of service being used - 4 (i.e., the ECHO data field in",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        370.96,
        540.02,
        382.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0025",
      "text": "the LS_ACC frame shall be equal in size to the ECHO data field size in the ECHO Request Se-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        382.96,
        540.12,
        394.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0026",
      "text": "quence).",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        394.96,
        134.88,
        406.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 7,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p045_s0027",
      "text": "4.2.4.4  Reply Sequence",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        550.96,
        209.29,
        562.08
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
